title: Girls Cross Country Roundup: Northmor takes fifth
text:
Girls Cross Country Roundup: Northmor takes fifth Marion Star staff report 3:21 p.m. EDT October 10, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Harding Invitational 
Northmor was fifth at the Harding Invitational (149 points), led by Kristen Duryea (6th, 19:30), Samantha Peters (25th, 20:39), Brooke Bennett (36th, 21:14), Reanne McDonald (41st, 21:28) and Sydney Jennette (48th, 21:52). 
Pleasant was seventh (205 poins), led by Hannah Peltier (17th, 20:11), Gabi Kowalczyk (21st, 20:19), Kamryn Kimmel (38th, 21:17), Alexis Kowalczyk (65th, 23:13) and Brooke Voisard (84th, 24:28). 
Marion Harding was eleventh (290 points), led by Cloie Riedlinger (30th, 21:01), Mackenzie Bays (40th, 21:21), Mia Tinnerello (72nd, 23:33), Kasey McDaniel (96th, 25:34) and Alexys Bell (101st, 26:04). 
River Valley was twelfth (328 points), led by Jaylynn Lewis (32nd, 21:03), Allison Lehner (69th, 23:29), Elle Hempstead (83rd, 24:27), Jensen Lewis (99th, 25:56) and Jordyn Jackson (105th, 26:33). 
Leading runners for Ridgedale were Michaela Fown (68th, 23:21) and Maddie Geyer (104th, 26:32). 
Mount Gilead Thill Invitational 
Mount Gilead was second at the Mount Gilead Thill Invitational (45 points), Jenna Shipman (1st, 20:04), Hannah Bush (4th, 20:41), Darcy Picker (11th, 21:42), Kelsey Snyder (14th, 22:07) and Micah James (18th, 22:53), 
Buckeye Valley was fourth (91 points), Kennedy Cramer (10th, 21:30), Michelle Culley (17th, 22:46), Analise Lajeunesse (21st, 23:05), Dominique Legg (25th, 23:39) and Nina Hilt (26th, 23:42). 
Cardington-Lincoln wsa fifth (139 points), led by Sage Brannon (23rd, 23:07), Alicia McElwee (24th, 23:38), Abbey Lorimer (39th, 25:19), Bailey Shafer (41st, 25:25) and Jessica Shook (47th, 26:04). 
Leading runners for Elgin were Sydney Pauley (15th, 22:32) and Mackenzie Ransome (57th, 28:57). Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1Lo9DkO More Stories
